🟩 PART 1: EXCEL DASHBOARD (LEFT SIDE)

🔹 A. KPI CARDS (Top Section)

These are the Key Performance Indicators (KPIs) — very important in business.

Total Revenue (₦245,860)
→ Total money generated from all sales

Average Sales (₦683.00)
→ Average value per transaction

Total Quantity (360)
→ Total number of items sold

Highest Sale (₦3,250)
→ Biggest single sale

Lowest Sale (₦50)
→ Smallest sale


👉 These KPIs give a quick summary of performance


🔹 B. FILTER PANEL (Left Sidebar)

These are called Slicers (Interactive Filters)

Region → Abuja, Lagos, Kano, etc.

Category → Electronics, Furniture, Appliances

Sales Rep → Names of staff

Payment Method → Cash, Card, Transfer

Date (Month) → Jan–Dec


👉 Purpose:

Allows users to filter data instantly

Makes dashboard interactive




🔹 C. REVENUE BY REGION (Bar Chart)

Shows how much each location generated.

Example:

Lagos → Highest revenue

Others → Lower


👉 Business Use:

Identify strong markets

Decide where to invest more




🔹 D. REVENUE BY CATEGORY (Pie Chart)

Breakdown of sales by product type:

Electronics → 71% (highest)

Furniture → 22%

Appliances → 7%


👉 Meaning:

Electronics is the most profitable category




🔹 E. SALES REP PERFORMANCE (Bar Chart)

Compares workers:

Ibrahim

Aisha

Musa

Fatima

Sadiya


👉 Purpose:

Measure employee performance

Helps with bonuses & promotions



🔹 F. TOP PRODUCTS TABLE

Lists best-selling items:

Examples:

Laptop

Smartphone

Office Chair


Shows:

Revenue

Quantity sold


👉 Helps identify:

High-demand products



🔹 G. MONTHLY REVENUE TREND (Line Chart)

Shows sales from January → December

👉 Purpose:

Detect growth or decline trends

Plan for future months




🔹 H. BUSINESS INSIGHTS (Important!)

This section explains findings:

Lagos generated highest revenue

Electronics dominate sales

Laptop & Smartphone are top products

Sales peak occurred mid-year


👉 This is where data turns into knowledge



